On Sunday, Ramaphosa announced that all gatherings of more than 100 people should be cancelled. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can also watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The Premier Soccer League (PSL)  held an urgent media briefing amid President Cyril Ramaphosa's announcement on COVID-19. On Sunday, Ramaphosa announced that all gatherings of more than 100 people should be cancelled. This as the country deals with internal transmission of the virus. The number of infected in South Africa has risen to 61 people. Ramaphosa has declared the pandemic a national disaster. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.